AMENDMENTS TO LB894
(Amendments to Standing Committee amendments, AM2004)
Introduced by DeKay, 40.
1 1. On page 5, line 28, after "88-529" insert "and, unless otherwise
2 provided, all fees received by the commission pursuant to the Grain
3 Dealer Act or the Grain Warehouse Act".
4 2. On page 8, line 5, strike "(1)" and insert "(1)(a)"; in line 6
5 strike "to be operated", show as stricken, and insert "that is not
6 licensed under the federal United States Warehouse Act"; and after line 9
7 insert the following new subdivision:
8 "(b) The commission shall not charge an annual license fee for a
9 warehouse that is licensed under the federal United States Warehouse
10 Act.".
11 3. On page 9, strike lines 17 through 30 and insert the following
12 new subdivisions:
13 "(3)(a) On or before December 1, 2026, the commission shall
14 establish the annual license fees that apply beginning July 1, 2027, to
15 warehouses that are not licensed under the federal United States
16 Warehouse Act and electronically submit a schedule of such fees to the
17 Clerk of the Legislature.
18 (b) Beginning in 2027, on or after July 1 of each year, the
19 commission may modify the annual license fees established under
20 subdivision (a) of this subsection.
21 (c) An annual license fee that is established or modified under this
22 subsection shall not exceed the fee established for the applicable
23 commodity in the 2025/2026 Rates Charged for AMS Services notice for
24 entities with a Commodity Credit Corporation agreement, as such notice
25 existed on January 1, 2026, that was published by the Agricultural
26 Marketing Service of the United States Department of Agriculture.".
